# .unallowed (gitignore-style patterns)
#
# Used by: scripts/check_unallowed_content.py
# Intent: project-local list of disallowed strings/patterns to prevent unintended
# leakage of environment-specific content into shared artifacts.
#
# Format notes (same style as .gitignore):
#   https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore
# - One pattern per line
# - # starts a comment
# - Blank lines are ignored
# - Supports glob wildcards: * ? []
# - Exception: ! negate/override rules are NOT supported
#
# See README.md in rtc-openclaw-project-mgmt for setup + usage.

# Add your organization-specific patterns below.
# examples:
# mycompany
# jane.doe@company.com
# @mycompany
